# Unique Agent Showcases: Claw Ecosystem

This plan detail the creation of 5 unique, standalone [index.html](file:///Users/mkazi/claw-ecosystem/index.html) showcases, one for each agent in the ecosystem.

## Core Directives
- **Data Ingestion**: Every [.md](file:///Users/mkazi/claw-ecosystem/AI-Agent-Nanobot/CLAUDE.md) file (Skills, Workflows, Docs, Use Cases) will be mapped to detailed UI sections.
- **Visual Uniqueness**: Completely different CSS, patterns, and menu structures for each site.
- **Portability**: Single-file [index.html](file:///Users/mkazi/claw-ecosystem/index.html) located in each agent's root directory.

## 1. 🐈 Nanobot: "The Minimalist Lab"
- **Theme**: Slate & Burnt Orange. Clean, grid-based typography.
- **Layout**: Floating content cards with large serif headings.
- **Menu**: Minimal top-bar with numeric navigation.
- **Special**: Python code-snippet reveals for core MCP tools.

## 2. 🐚 NanoClaw: "The Swarm Interface"
- **Theme**: Deep Purple & Indigo. Holographic glassmorphism.
- **Layout**: Layered circular nodes representing agent swarms.
- **Menu**: Floating radial menu in the bottom-right.
- **Special**: Interactive Swarm Viz showing container-isolated groups.

## 3. 🦞 OpenClaw: "The Command HQ"
- **Theme**: Navy Blue & Steel. Dashboard architecture.
- **Layout**: Multi-column dashboard with live-updating stat simulations.
- **Menu**: Persistent vertical sidebar with folding sections.
- **Special**: "RALPH methodology" step-through visualizer.

## 4. 🦐 PicoClaw: "The Edge Terminal"
- **Theme**: Emerald & Pitch Black. Cyberpunk/CRT Aesthetic.
- **Layout**: Vertical terminal feed with scanline overlays.
- **Menu**: Command-line interface emulator (type commands to navigate).
- **Special**: Real-time "Heartbeat" pulse animation.

## 5. 🦀 ZeroClaw: "The High-Perf Engine"
- **Theme**: Crimson & Charcoal. Brutalist angles (45-degree slashes).
- **Layout**: Horizontal segmenting with fast, high-contrast imagery.
- **Menu**: Corner-slash navigation buttons.
- **Special**: Rust Trait performance comparison charts.

## Implementation Steps
1. **Scanning**: Read all [.md](file:///Users/mkazi/claw-ecosystem/AI-Agent-Nanobot/CLAUDE.md) files in each repo to ensure 100% data coverage.
2. **Scaffolding**: Build the 5 unique [index.html](file:///Users/mkazi/claw-ecosystem/index.html) files with embedded CSS/JS.
3. **Refining**: Apply premium UI/UX Pro Max animations (Intersection Observers, GSAP-like CSS transitions).
4. **Linking**: Ensure internal links point to local repo docs correctly.
